author: 壹蘋新聞網
title: 美人餐桌菜鳥時期慘被當跑腿小妹　自認神經質狠嗆老闆：我只會買咖啡
text:
于美人氣憤表示：「我明明招生能力也不錯，為什麼是我去買？」更透露自己會暗中較勁，故意號召學生同一天報名，製造排隊人潮，並嗆上司們：「我只會買咖啡啊。」坦言當時非常神經質，把委屈都藏在心裡，但老闆根本不知道她在傷心什麼。
「跟我錄影最好注意一點！」楊皓如直言，如果主持人在她講話時，不理會，甚至打哈欠，她就會覺得對方不喜歡她，並開始戰戰兢兢地試探對方是否討厭自己。黃鐙輝也補充，自己的徒弟曾子余，跟楊皓如一樣敏感。他透露，曾帶曾子余去試鏡，演出變性人，但子余非常排斥，甚至打退堂鼓。最後，那個角色反而在國際影展、金馬獎，入圍多項獎項，讓他扼腕不已。也讓黃鐙輝困惑地說：「我真的不懂為何要畫地自限，為何一定要覺得自己不行。」于美人聽了則回嗆：「也有可能是老闆有問題。」

author: Stefanie Davis
title: Balancing medicine and music: Kitchener nurse nominated for first Juno award
text:
[Skip to main content](#main)
Balancing medicine and music: Kitchener nurse nominated for first Juno award
A Kitchener nurse was on shift at Grand River Hospital when she got the call letting her know the Junos were considering her album for nomination.
“She said ‘I’m calling from the Junos and I just like silent screamed, because you know, you’re at work,” singer-songwriter Tuzee Arndt said, with a laugh.
The artist, who goes by Tuzee for her music, has since been named an official nominee in the Contemporary Christian/Gospel Album of the Year category for her album titled Alive.
“It’s hard to describe. It’s just amazing and what I’ve worked so hard for and it’s been a journey actually getting my music out,” said Tuzee.
While putting out that album, Tuzee has continued working as a full-time nurse.
“There’s a lot about nursing that I love,” Tuzee said. “I become a voice for people who do not have one and I become hope for people who do not have hope.”
Before her love for nursing was her love for music. It started when she was growing up in Liberia, singing at church with her family.
“Music has always been in my family. My dad sang, my whole family sang. I’m the fourth of seven, so sometimes it was like a competition in our house,” Tuzee said.
When she moved by herself from Liberia to Canada, music became a source of comfort for her without having her family nearby.
In 2019, she took the next step – recording and releasing her own songs.
“I just woke up one day and I’m like ‘I’m going to record this song,’” she said.
The first song she recorded was called Shine, which is featured on her album Alive.
Shortly after that came out, the pandemic hit. Health care got busier and she used music as an outlet.
“Believe me, I’d come home some days and I’m like ‘okay, I just want to sleep,’” Tuzee said. “But then there are those other days when I get home and went through a great day, and there’s so much in my head to write. So it really balances out.”
Some songs, including Change Is on the Way, came from nursing during the pandemic.
Tuzee said her day job often inspires her music.
Her friend and fellow nurse Zephania Alexander has watched Tuzee juggle it all.
“I don’t know how she does it,” Alexander said.
“After a 12 hour shift, I’m done. I go home, I want to watch TV and lay on the couch. That’s it. So I can’t believe that she’s not only working as a nurse, but she’s a mom, she has a family, and then also on top of that she’s singing, song writing, making music videos and all of that,” said Alexander.
That hard work has paid off with her Juno nomination. Tuzee was named Gospel Music Association female vocalist of the year. Next, she’ll be travelling to Halifax for the first time to attend the Junos on March 24.
Regardless of the outcome, she said she’s honoured to even be nominated.
“But hopefully it’s a win,” Tuzee said, with a laugh.
Without the support of her family, friends and producer, Tuzee said she wouldn’t be able to do all she can.

author: Shaun Polczer
title: WATCH: NDP’s Angus calls Smith a spokesperson for those ‘burning the planet’
text: The ever-affable Charlie Angus never seems to disappoint when it comes to outrageous antics in the name of his one-man climate crusade against Alberta’s oil companies.The outgoing NDP MP for Timmins-James Bay was up to his usual shenanigans on Thursday, after an unhinged media rant against the CEO of Calgary-based Suncor Energy and Alberta Premier Danielle Smith, whom he called a “spokesperson” for those who want “to burn the planet.”“If you look at any of the major lawsuits that have come in against big oil, you see a real clear pattern. They knew they were burning the planet. They knew in the 1980s they were burning the planet,” he began..“What concerns me at this time is how provocative Big Oil CEOs like (Suncor’s) Rich Kruger are. They're asking to increase production in the tar sands which has the highest greenhouse gas emissions levels on the planet. In fact, we heard yesterday, their spokesperson Danielle Smith said she wants to double production in the tar sands. This has got to be dealt with.”Angus made the comments on the way in to a meeting of the House environment committee which will feature appearances from several Calgary energy CEOs via videoconference — including Kruger — to testify on ‘profits and emissions reduction efforts in Canada’s oil and gas industry’.Angus appeared alongside NDP colleague Laurel Collins, the party’s climate change critic who called on the Liberal government to “make big polluters pay their fare share.”The solution? Angus called for the government of Canada to support the UN and Secretary General Antonio Guiterres’ call to ban oil and gas advertising.“This is the big tobacco moment for oil and gas. We have to hold these companies accountable. We're calling for an end to the false advertising of Big Oil and Gas. It's time we started to hold them accountable for the destruction of our future and our children's future.”Angus’ private members bill, C-372 or the Fossil Fuel Advertising Act, would have imposed jail sentences for oil executives.

author: Redacción Gestión
title: Nvidia | IA | Vehículos eléctricos | satélites | chips | Desarrollo de China por la hegemonía | OPINION | GESTIÓN
text: Ricardo Valcárcel Escribe: Ricardo Valcárcel, analista económico. [China ](https://gestion.pe/noticias/china/)está empeñada en convertirse en el líder mundial. Obviamente, [EE.UU.](https://gestion.pe/noticias/estados-unidos/), el actual país hegemónico, está haciendo todo lo posible para impedirlo o, al menos, retrasar tal cambio de mando que parece inevitable. Un pilar del desarrollo de China es la [innovación](https://gestion.pe/noticias/innovacion/), basada principalmente en la educación y en la investigación, para aumentar su [competitividad ](https://gestion.pe/noticias/competitividad/) [económica](https://gestion.pe/economia/?gad_source=1&gclid=EAIaIQobChMIwPGipfj3hwMVIQytBh2DKhbQEAAYASAAEgI6CfD_BwE/). En cuanto a la educación, tomemos la referencia de la Universidad de Leiden, la cual mide diferentes factores para clasificar cuáles son las mejores universidades del mundo. En el campo de todas las ciencias y su impacto científico, de las 15 más destacadas, 13 son de China; solo la Universidad de [Harvard ](https://gestion.pe/noticias/harvard/)y la de Toronto están incluidas. [LEA TAMBIÉN: En el Perú sí se pasa hambre] En la categoría de ciencias de la salud y biomédicas, China tiene 8 de las 10 mejores universidades del mundo. En las ciencias de la vida y de la tierra, cuenta con 7 de las 10 principales universidades. Algo notable es que, en el área de las matemáticas y cibernética, China posee las 25 principales universidades del planeta. ¡Asombroso! En la clasificación de la ingeniería y ciencias físicas, China cuenta con 24 de las 25 universidades más destacadas del mundo; solo la Universidad de Tokio ocupa un lugar. En la categoría de las ciencias sociales y humanidades, China no tiene ninguna universidad sobresaliente, ya que todas las 25 primeras son de los países occidentales desarrollados. Esta superioridad manifiesta de China en la educación se traduce, a través de la investigación y el desarrollo, en toda la producción de bienes y servicios, con mejor calidad y menor costo. Un grupo de expertos del Instituto de Política Estratégica de Australia, en un reciente estudio, concluyó que China lidera en 37 de 44 tecnologías críticas a nivel global. [LEA TAMBIÉN: Bolsas emergentes, crecimiento y diversidad] Tomemos como ejemplo la inteligencia artificial generativa (IAG), aquella que inventa algo nuevo al proporcionarle algunos datos de entrada, combinándolos con información adicional fruto del “entrenamiento” masivo. Así, puede crear con facilidad una imagen a partir de un texto. En la lista de poseedores de patentes de propiedad intelectual de la IAG, entre las primeras diez entidades con mayor cantidad, están cuatro de China: Tencent, Baidu, Ping An Insurance y la Chinese Academy of Sciences. Actualmente, China produce más patentes de IAG que todos los países del mundo tomados en conjunto. Sin embargo, los modelos más sofisticados y avanzados de IAG siguen siendo de corporaciones de EE.UU. China podría haber avanzado mucho más en IAG, pero EE.UU. le ha impedido contar con todo el poder de cómputo, con una serie de regulaciones y prohibiciones, que le impiden acceder a los chips más modernos. [LEA TAMBIÉN: Precisiones necesarias en la elección de supervisores SST y delegados HSL] La estadounidense Nvidia es el coloso mundial en la producción de chips de IA. EE.UU. le ha prohibido vender a China los chips más potentes bajo pena de sanciones. Sin embargo, China ha reaccionado rápidamente. Hasta hace un año, se estimaba que China lograría alcanzar la potencia de los chips H2O de Nvidia en 10 años. Pues bien, hace pocos meses, Huawei lanzó chips superiores en 20% de potencia a los H2O. Claro, Nvidia ya está lanzando al mercado chips aún más potentes, toda una batalla en este campo. Otro terreno en que se compite es el servicio de internet de cobertura mundial, vía un conjunto interconectado de satélites. Primero fue la estadounidense SpaceX, de Elon Musk, quien creó Starlink en 2019. En la actualidad, tiene en órbita 6,700 satélites y espera completar 12,000 en su proyecto. China acaba de iniciar una propuesta propia similar, llamada “Thousand Sails”, que llegaría a tener 15,000 satélites. Otro espacio de combate está en los vehículos. Por muchas décadas, los carros que los chinos compraban eran de marcas extranjeras, como Buick, Volkswagen, BMW o Toyota, porque eran de calidad superior a los fabricados localmente. [LEA TAMBIÉN: Empresas: ¿Cómo enfrentar una crisis de crecimiento?] Eso ha terminado bruscamente. Ford, General Motors y otros fabricantes alemanes, coreanos, franceses y japoneses han sentido la sacudida al perder su rentable mercado. Ahora, el 62% de los carros comprados por consumidores chinos son fabricados domésticamente. Y más de la mitad son eléctricos o híbridos. Es fácil de comprenderlo cuando los vehículos BYD cuestan un 30% menos y son de mayor calidad, gracias a una integración vertical, gran productividad y algunos subsidios gubernamentales. También el combate se da en el ámbito financiero. Actualmente, la banca internacional ejecuta mayoritariamente sus transacciones usando el sistema Swift, una sociedad cooperativa de 11,000 bancos, supervisada por varios países europeos, EE.UU. y Japón. [LEA TAMBIÉN: Información digital: “Cada vez nos resulta más difícil leer textos que sean más extensos que un tuit”] Varios otros países consideran un peligro estar supeditados al sistema Swift para su comercio, inversiones, remesas y cualquier otra transacción financiera. Es así que los países que conforman el BRICS están estructurando otro sistema, ajeno al Swift, que no usará el dólar estadounidense para sus transacciones. China y Rusia lideran este proyecto. Quedan pocas dudas de que China, en el largo plazo, será el país hegemónico destronando a EE.UU. En ese tránsito, ya estamos viendo, incluso en el Perú, las estrategias geopolíticas que siguen ambos combatientes para aliarse con muchos países. Es necesario, para los intereses del Perú, estar atentos para aprovechar las oportunidades y afrontar los contratiempos que se van a presentar en esa lucha, pues de otro modo terminaremos pagando con la tuya y con la mía, sometidos a una de las partes Comienza a destacar en el mundo empresarial recibiendo las noticias más exclusivas del día en tu bandeja [Aquí]. Si aún no tienes una cuenta, [Regístrate gratis]y sé parte de nuestra comunidad.

author: @infobae
title: Descubren un nuevo titanosaurio en la Patagonia que podría revolucionar el curso de la paleontología
text: Un nuevo descubrimiento significativo sacudió a la paleontología. Un equipo de investigadores del CONICET encontraron los restos fósiles de un tipo de titanosaurio denominado Titanomachya gimenezi, que vivió hace unos 66 millones de años, al final del período Cretácico. Se estima que pesaba aproximadamente 7 toneladas y era diez veces más pequeño que otros de su especie.

author: Daniel Hampton
title: 'Dangerous': Mitch McConnell stops short of naming Trump in attack on 'American right'
text:
Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell (R-KY) is worried his own party will repeat mistakes from the 1930s — and warned about it in an opinion piece Thursday in The New York Times.
McConnell — who endorsed former President Donald Trump's 2024 campaign in March — kicked off his piece lamenting that Europe and the United States met a "militant authoritarian with appeasement or naïve neglect" in the '30s, and said today America and its allies face "some of the
gravest threats to our security since Axis forces marched across Europe and the Pacific."
While he made no mention that Trump's own rhetoric has
raised alarm bells and been compared to that of authoritarian governments — as recently as this week — McConnell said some of those same forces that derailed a response in the 1930s have returned.
McConnell pointed to problems he sees "here at home" — and took a shot at the foreign policy stances of some of the louder voices in the GOP.
"Some vocal corners of the American right are trying to resurrect the discredited brand of prewar isolationism and deny the basic value of the alliance system that has kept the postwar peace," McConnell wrote. "This dangerous proposition rivals the American left’s longstanding allergy to military spending in its potential to make America less safe."
ALSO READ:
How Donald Trump could run for president — and lead the nation — from prison
The Republican stalwart warned his party that it shouldn't take a major catastrophe like Pearl Harbor to "wake today’s isolationists from the delusion that regional conflicts have no consequences for the world’s most powerful and prosperous nation."
"With global power comes global interests and global responsibilities," McConnell wrote.
Other major Republican leaders have also
pushed back against isolationism in history, including Gen. Dwight D. Eisenhower, former President Ronald Reagan, and former President George W. Bush.
McConnell's piece comes after a poll last fall from the Chicago Council on Global Affairs found that for the first time in nearly 50 years, "a majority of Republicans in 2023 said it would be best for the future of the United States to
stay out of — rather than take an active part in — in world affairs."
The finding represents a major shift in public opinion in the last decade, the organization said, when Republican supporters were more likely than Democrats to "favor an active role abroad."

title: ಹುಷಾರು… ಕರ್ನಾಟಕ ಉತ್ತರ ಭಾರತದಂತಾಗುವ ಸಾಧ್ಯತೆ; ಬಹುತೇಕ ಜಿಲ್ಲೆಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಹೆಚ್ಚಾಗಲಿದೆ ಚಳಿ!
text:
Weather Update: ರಾಷ್ಟ್ರ ರಾಜಧಾನಿ ದೆಹಲಿ ಸೇರಿದಂತೆ ಉತ್ತರ ಭಾರತದಲ್ಲಿ ಆಗಾಗ ಚಳಿ-ಶೀತಗಾಳಿ ಜಾಸ್ತಿಯಾಗುವ ಸುದ್ದಿ ಕೇಳಿರುತ್ತೀರಿ. ಆದರೀಗ ಅಂಥ ಪರಿಸ್ಥಿತಿ ಕರ್ನಾಟಕಕ್ಕೂ ಬರುತ್ತಿದೆ. ರಾಜ್ಯದ ಬಹುತೇಕ ಜಿಲ್ಲೆಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಬೆಳಿಗ್ಗೆ ಮತ್ತು ಸಂಜೆ ಸಿಕ್ಕಾಪಟ್ಟೆ ಚಳಿ ಹೆಚ್ಚಾಗಲಿದೆ ಎನ್ನುವ ಮಾಹಿತಿಗಳು ಕೇಳಿಬರುತ್ತಿವೆ.
[ಹವಾಮಾನ ವೈಪರೀತ್ಯ ](https://zeenews.india.com/kannada/photo-gallery/three-chief-ministers-of-karnataka-have-completed-their-full-five-year-terms-274697)ಎಲ್ಲಿ? ಯಾವ ರೀತಿ ಆಗುತ್ತದೆ ಎನ್ನುವುದನ್ನು ಅಂದಾಜು ಮಾಡುವುದೇ ಕಷ್ಟವಾಗುತ್ತಿದೆ. ಕರ್ನಾಟಕ ಹಿಂದೆಂದೂ ಯದ್ವಾತದ್ವಾ ಚಳಿ ಮತ್ತು ಶೀತಗಾಳಿಯನ್ನು ಎದುರಿಸುತ್ತಿರಲಿಲ್ಲ. ಆದರೀಗ ಹವಮಾನ ಇಲಾಖೆಯ ಮಾಹಿತಿಗಳ ಪ್ರಕಾರ ಮುಂದಿನ ದಿನಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಕರ್ನಾಟಕದ ಬಹುತೇಕ ಜಿಲ್ಲೆಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಮುಂಜಾನೆ ಮತ್ತು ಸಂಜೆ ಮಂಜು ಬೀಳುವ ಪ್ರಮಾಣ ಜಾಸ್ತಿಯಾಗುತ್ತದೆ.
ಇದನ್ನೂ ಓದಿ- [ಹಾಸ್ಟೆಲ್ ನಲ್ಲಿ ವಿದ್ಯಾರ್ಥಿ ಅನುಮಾನಸ್ಪದ ಸಾವು: ಪ್ರಾಂಶುಪಾಲ ಸೇರಿ ಇಬ್ಬರು ಅಮಾನತು](https://zeenews.india.com/kannada/karnataka/puc-student-suspicious-death-in-morarji-desai-residential-school-two-people-including-principal-suspended-274845)
ಮುಂಜಾನೆ ಮತ್ತು ಸಾಯಂಕಾಲ ಮಂಜು ಕೂಡಿದ ವಾತಾವರಣ ನಿರ್ಮಾಣವಾಗುವುದರಿಂದ ಹವಾಮಾನ ತಣ್ಣಾಗಾಗುತ್ತದೆ. ಗಾಳಿ, [ಶೀತಗಾಳಿ](https://zeenews.india.com/kannada/karnataka/karnataka-media-academy-award-list-2024-published-274690)ಯಾಗಿ ಪರಿವರ್ತಿತವಾಗುತ್ತದೆ ಮತ್ತು ಚಳಿಯ ಪ್ರಮಾಣದಲ್ಲಿ ಗಣನೀಯವಾಗಿ ಏರಿಕೆಯಾಗುತ್ತದೆ ಎಂದು ತಿಳಿದುಬಂದಿದೆ.

title: Tory MP suggests ‘crap parents’ behind most of town’s struggling children - Press and Journal
text:
Tory MP suggests ‘crap parents’ behind most of town’s struggling children By Press Association December 28 2023, 9.19pm Share Tory MP suggests ‘crap parents’ behind most of town’s struggling children Share via Facebook Twitter Whatsapp Messenger Linkedin Email Post link https://www.pressandjournal.co.uk/politics/6310566/tory-mp-suggests-crap-parents-behind-most-of-towns-struggling-children/ Copy Link James Daly (David Woolfall/UK Parliament/PA)
A Conservative MP has been criticised for suggesting most children who struggle in an English town are the “products of crap parents”.
James Daly was accused by his Labour rival of “insulting the parenting skills of people in Bury” after the remark was made in a newspaper piece analysing election prospects for the Greater Manchester town.
Mr Daly, speaking to the i newspaper, stressed the importance of “stability” offered by the family unit as he outlined what the New Conservatives group of MPs stands for.
The Bury North MP said: “I think New Conservatives represent very much working-class conservatism.
“We’re not a strange right-wing sect. It’s just people who want to give people the best chance to succeed and thrive in life.
“When you think about the family, it’s about stability.
“Most of the kids who struggle in Bury are the products of crap parents and so what do we do to try to address that issue?
“On the left it would just be we’ll throw money at this and hope something sticks, somebody like me thinks about this more fundamentally.”
James Frith, Labour’s prospective parliamentary candidate for Bury North, said: “It is revealing to see how little James Daly thinks of his own constituents.
“Rather than insulting the parenting skills of people in Bury, he should look closer to home.
“Over the last 13 years the Conservatives have failed to grow our economy, protect our public services or provide opportunities for young people in Bury and across the UK.”
